The paper deals with semantic segmentation using convolutional neural networks, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed reverse attention network (RAN) architecture involves training the network to capture the opposite concept of a target class, which is a novel approach in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the RAN in semantic segmentation, which involves learning semantic features and classification, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The RAN architecture involves multiple branches and attention mechanisms, which are common in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) concepts such as attention, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
